<subSubSection id="C3106500FFA7FFE4E38FF9BC93637DD9" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB5368BFFA7FFE4E38FF9BC93637DD9" blockId="1.[151,1437,297,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E38FF9BC96A27D45" bold="true" box="[199,455,1629,1656]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54B18829FFA7FFE4E298F9BF95587D4A" box="[464,573,1629,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Holotype</typeStatus>
: total length, 9.9; length of pronotum, 1.9; width of pronotum, 3.2; humeral width, 3.8; length of elytra, 6.8. 
<typeStatus id="54B18829FFA7FFE4E14CF96095147DA1" box="[516,625,1666,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Paratypes</typeStatus>
male: total length, 9.0–11.1; length of pronotum, 1.8–2.3; width of pronotum, 3.0–3.7; humeral width, 3.6–4.7; length of elytra, 6.3–7.7. 
<typeStatus id="54B18829FFA7FFE4E0DFF944949C7DFD" box="[919,1017,1702,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Paratype</typeStatus>
female: total length, 10.7; length of pronotum, 2.1; width of pronotum, 3.6; humeral width, 4.3; length of elytra, 7.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3106500FFA7FFE4E38FF90C964D7C6D" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB5368BFFA7FFE4E38FF90C964D7C6D" blockId="1.[151,1437,297,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E38FF90C962B7C35" bold="true" box="[199,334,1774,1800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is allusive to the stain of white setae covering the lateral tubercles of the pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13312A0EFFA7FFE4E3A7F8F396567C11" box="[239,307,1809,1836]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[188,1396,237,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1400,237,1850]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Plistonax albituberculatus Silva Júnior &amp; Souza sp. nov., holotype male.1. Dorsal habitus; 2. Ventral habitus; 3. Lateral habitus; 4, Head, frontal view; 5. Prothorax, dorsal view; 6. Labels; 7. Elytra, detail of punctation and setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772443/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), which is the main feature that distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E073F8F393067C16" authority="Júnior &amp; Haseyama &amp; Souza, 2019" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Haseyama &amp; Souza" authorityYear="2019" box="[827,1123,1809,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albituberculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E073F8F393067C16" box="[827,1123,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Plistonax albituberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E722F8F093A17C11" bold="true" box="[1130,1220,1810,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24D57E2FFA7FFE4E722F8F093A17C11" box="[1130,1220,1810,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3106500FFA7FFE7E38FF8BB94247BEA" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB5368BFFA7FFE7E38FF8BB94247BEA" blockId="1.[151,1437,297,2016]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,153,215]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E38FF8BB962A7C49" bold="true" box="[199,335,1881,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Comments.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E1D3F8BB93157C49" authority="(Zajciw, 1964)" baseAuthorityName="Zajciw" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[667,1136,1881,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bialbomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E1D3F8BB94A37C4E" box="[667,966,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Plistonax bialbomaculatus</emphasis>
(Zajciw, 1964)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E7ECF8BB96197CAA" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 2006" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E7ECF8BB923A7C4E" box="[1188,1375,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Plistonax rafaeli</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 
<quantity id="4CF29B6EFFA7FFE4E20CF89F96197CAA" box="[324,380,1917,1943]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0952399999999995" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" unit="in" value="2006.0">2006</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, body size, and by having elytral apex truncate and median-basal crests reaching approximately half of the elytra. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E1BDF84094AA7C86" baseAuthorityName="Zajciw" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[757,975,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bialbomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E1BDF84094AA7C86" box="[757,975,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">P. bialbomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E742F84093167C86" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2006" box="[1034,1139,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E742F84093167C86" box="[1034,1139,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">P. rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are only known from the Amazon region. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D08FFA7FFE4E21DF82795187CE2" authority="Júnior &amp; Haseyama &amp; Souza, 2019" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Haseyama &amp; Souza" authorityYear="2019" box="[341,637,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plistonax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albituberculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E21DF82795187CE2" box="[341,637,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">Plistonax albituberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97EEA99FFA7FFE4E1CDF82495BA7CDD" bold="true" box="[645,735,1990,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24D57E2FFA7FFE4E1CDF82495BA7CDD" box="[645,735,1990,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="393" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from all species of the genus by having, together, the lateral tubercles of the pronotum and tarsomeres I and V densely covered by white setae, and abdominal tergite V without sexual dimorphism related to its length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
